snippet.textDisplay: CHIA is not supposed to race through NAND storage as is specified in the video as far as I can tell by reading the whitepaper. It writes data(plotted solutions) onto the allocated space once, which are then read over and over to see if one of the plotted solutions written to the drive is close to the final solution, which it then relays back to the network. NAND only degrades from write-cycles, not read-cycles.
